properties.areaDesc: Coastal waters from Chincoteague to Parramore Island VA out 20 nm; Coastal waters from Fenwick Island DE to Chincoteague VA out 20 nm
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 7 at 10:50AM EST until January 8 at 7:00PM EST by NWS Wakefield VA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest winds 20 to 25 kt with gusts up to 35 kt
tonight. Winds become westerly and diminish to 15 to 20 kt
overnight. West winds increase to 25 to 30 kt with gusts up to
40 kt late Wednesday morning through Wednesday evening. Waves 4
to 6 feet expected.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Fenwick Island DE to Chincoteague
VA out 20 nm and Coastal waters from Chincoteague to Parramore
Island VA out 20 nm.

* WHEN...From 5 PM this afternoon to 7 PM EST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 5 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 7 PM EST WEDNESDAY
